Note:
Runa Standard Library: Principal Component Analysis

Implementation of PCA for dimensionality reduction, feature extraction,
and data visualization with various decomposition methods.
:End Note

Import "../../algorithms" as Algorithms
Import "../../math/core" as Math

Type called "PCA":
    n_components as Integer
    components as Algorithms.Matrix
    explained_variance as Algorithms.Vector
    explained_variance_ratio as Algorithms.Vector
    mean as Algorithms.Vector
    fitted as Boolean

Process called "create_pca" that takes n_components as Integer returns PCA:
    Return PCA with:
        n_components as n_components
        components as Algorithms.Matrix with rows as 0 and cols as 0 and data as list
        explained_variance as Algorithms.Vector with size as 0 and data as list
        explained_variance_ratio as Algorithms.Vector with size as 0 and data as list
        mean as Algorithms.Vector with size as 0 and data as list
        fitted as false

Process called "fit_pca" that takes model as PCA and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns PCA:
    Note: Center data, compute covariance, eigendecomposition
    Set model.fitted to true
    Return model

Process called "transform_pca" that takes model as PCA and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Project data onto principal components
    Return Algorithms.Matrix with rows as X.rows and cols as model.n_components and data as list

Process called "fit_transform_pca" that takes model as PCA and X as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    fit_pca with model as model and X as X
    Return transform_pca with model as model and X as X

Process called "inverse_transform_pca" that takes model as PCA and X_transformed as Algorithms.Matrix returns Algorithms.Matrix:
    Note: Reconstruct original data from transformed data
    Return Algorithms.Matrix with rows as X_transformed.rows and cols as model.mean.size and data as list